<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

									*Patient Health Questionnaire (PHQ-9)*
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 04-02-2021
last updated:  02-25-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-25-2022 Millisecond Software
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements a computerized version of the Patient Health Questionnaire (PHQ-9)
by Kroenke et al (2001).


Reference:
Kroenke, K., Spitzer, R. L., & Williams, J. B. W. (2001). The PHQ-9 - Validity of a brief 
depression severity measure. Journal of General Internal Medicine, 16, 606-613.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

The scale consists of 9 4-point Likert scale items.
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes < 1 min to complete.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________		
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'phq_9.iqdat'

date, time:							date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  		 with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:								the Inquisit build 

q*_response:						response given (in assigned values)
									Scale: q1-q9: 0 (Not at all) - 3 (Nearly every day)
									Scale: q10: 0 (Not difficult at all) - 3 (Extremely difficult)
									
q*_latency:							how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
									question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)


(2) Summary data file: 'phq_9_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
									
								
DepressedMoodOrAnhedonia:		1 = at least one answer for q1 (anhedonia) or q2 (depressed mood) 
								was a '2' or a '3 (>= more than half the days)
								0 = otherwise
												
DepressionSymptonsCounter:		counts the number of '2' or '3' responses (>= more than half the days)
								for q1-q8 as well as any response other than 0 for q9
												
								Major Depression if
								1. 'DepressedMoodOrAnhedonia' = 1 AND
								2.  DepressionSymptonsCounter >= 5
												
								Other Depression if
								1. 'DepressedMoodOrAnhedonia' = 1 AND
								2.  2 <= DepressionSymptonsCounter < 5
												
									
phq9_severityScore:				Total Score (adds up all valid response values from q1-q9; range: 0-27)
								1-4 Minimal depression
								5-9 Mild depression
								10-14 Moderate depression
								15-19 Moderately severe depression
								20-27 Severe depression 

individual responses: 
Scale: q1-q9: 0 (Not at all) - 3 (Nearly every day)
Scale: q10: 0 (Not difficult at all) - 3 (Extremely difficult)

radiobuttons.q1.response to 
q10 (*Note: q10 is only presented if participant has indicated any 
possible depression response (response > 0) for any of the nine questions. If 
all responses = 0, q10 is automatically scored with a 0)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:


</usermanual>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Over the <u>last 2 weeks</u>, how often have you been bothered by any of the following problems?<br>
"
</parameters>

**************************************************************************************************************
				!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = black
/ screencolor = white
</defaults>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

***********************
summary data file
***********************
<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, 
script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId,
script.elapsedTime, script.completed,

expressions.DepressedMoodOrAnhedonia, values.DepressionSymptonsCounter,
values.phq9_severityScore,
radiobuttons.q1.response,
radiobuttons.q2.response,
radiobuttons.q3.response,
radiobuttons.q4.response,
radiobuttons.q5.response,
radiobuttons.q6.response,
radiobuttons.q7.response,
radiobuttons.q8.response,
radiobuttons.q9.response,
expressions.q10
)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES/EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************


<expressions>
/DepressedMoodOrAnhedonia = {
	if (radiobuttons.q1.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q1.response == 3 || radiobuttons.q2.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q2.response == 3){
		1;
	} else {
		0;
	}
}
/countDepressionSymptoms = {
	values.DepressionSymptonsCounter = 0;
	if (radiobuttons.q1.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q1.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q2.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q2.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q3.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q3.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q4.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q4.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q5.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q5.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q6.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q6.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q7.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q7.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q8.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q8.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q9.response == 1 || radiobuttons.q9.response == 2 || radiobuttons.q9.response == 3){
		values.DepressionSymptonsCounter += 1;
	}	
}	

/phq9_severityScore = {
	values.phq9_severityScore = 0;
	if (radiobuttons.q1.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q1.response;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q2.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q2.response;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q3.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q3.response;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q4.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q4.response;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q5.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q5.response;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q6.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q6.response;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q7.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q7.response;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q8.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q8.response;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q9.response <= 3){
		values.phq9_severityScore += radiobuttons.q9.response;
	}
}

/q10 = {
	if (radiobuttons.q1.response == 0 &&
	radiobuttons.q2.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q3.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q4.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q5.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q6.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q7.response == 0 &&
	radiobuttons.q8.response == 0 &&
	radiobuttons.q9.response == 0){
		0;
	} else {
		radiobuttons.q10.response;
	}
}
</expressions>

<values>
/completed = 0
/DepressionSymptonsCounter = 0
/phq9_severityScore = 0
</values>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "1. Little interest or pleasure in doing things"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2>
/caption = "2. Feeling down, depressed or hopeless"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3>
/caption = "3. Trouble falling asleep, staying asleep, or sleeping too much"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4>
/caption = "4. Feeling tired or having little energy"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5>
/caption = "5. Poor appetite or overeating"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6>
/caption = "6. Feeling bad about yourself - or that you're a failure or have let yourself or your family down"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7>
/caption = "7. Trouble concentrating on things, such as reading the newspaper or watching television"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8>
/caption = "8. Moving or speaking so slowly that other people could have noticed. Or, the opposite- being so fidgety or restless that you have been moving around a lot more than usual"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9>
/caption = "9. Thoughts that you would be better off dead or of hurting yourself in some way"
/ options = ("Not~nAt All", "Several ~nDays", "More than ~nHalf the Days", "Nearly ~nEvery Day")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10>
/caption = "10. If you checked off any problems, how difficult have those problems made it for you to do your work, take care of things at home, or get along with other people?
"
/ options = ("Not difficult ~nat all", "Somewhat ~ndifficult", "Very ~ndifficult", "Extremely ~ndifficult")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage phq_9_1>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q1, q2, q3]
</surveypage>

<surveypage phq_9_2>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q4, q5, q6]
</surveypage>

<surveypage phq_9_3>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q7, q8, q9]
</surveypage>

<surveypage phq_9_4>
/ skip = [
	radiobuttons.q1.response == 0 &&
	radiobuttons.q2.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q3.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q4.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q5.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q6.response == 0 &&	
	radiobuttons.q7.response == 0 &&
	radiobuttons.q8.response == 0 &&
	radiobuttons.q9.response == 0;	
]
/ questions = [1 = q10]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
- presents the surveypages
- to take pictures of each screen set /screencapture = true

<survey phq_9>
/pages = [
	1 = phq_9_1;
	2 = phq_9_2;
	3 = phq_9_3;
	4 = phq_9_4;
]
/screencapture = false
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, true, false, false, 5, 1)
/ subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 2%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = false
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (20%, 5%)
/ finishlabel = "Submit"
/ onblockend = [
	expressions.countDepressionSymptoms;
	expressions.phq9_severityScore;
]
</survey>

**************************************************************************************************************
												End of File
